WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.952 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.952 --> 00:00:30.104 align:middle line:90%


00:00:30.104 --> 00:00:32.479 align:middle line:84%
>> They vow they are going to
be different with their own

00:00:32.479 --> 00:00:33.120 align:middle line:90%
children.

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:34.370 align:middle line:10%
They're going to
give them free reign

00:00:34.370 --> 00:00:35.662 align:middle line:10%
and encourage them to have fun.

00:00:35.662 --> 00:00:37.250 align:middle line:10%
And they act just
as overprotective

00:00:37.250 --> 00:00:40.580 align:middle line:10%
as their own parents
because they feel

00:00:40.580 --> 00:00:42.740 align:middle line:10%
they have hurt their parent.

00:00:42.740 --> 00:00:44.390 align:middle line:10%
And therefore, they
feel they deserve

00:00:44.390 --> 00:00:47.180 align:middle line:10%
to be hurt in return
by their own children.

00:00:47.180 --> 00:00:48.920 align:middle line:10%
>> You did it again, didn't you?

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:53.690 align:middle line:10%
So did I. Broke every
New Year's resolution.

00:00:53.690 --> 00:00:55.490 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, it only
takes two weeks

00:00:55.490 --> 00:00:57.770 align:middle line:90%
before you start breaking them.

00:00:57.770 --> 00:01:02.245 align:middle line:84%
Why do we behave
in ways we hate?

00:01:02.245 --> 00:01:03.370 align:middle line:90%
We have help for you today.

00:01:03.370 --> 00:01:07.380 align:middle line:84%
We have Dr. Irwin Gootnick,
who has written a book called

00:01:07.380 --> 00:01:12.270 align:middle line:84%
by the name "Why You
Behave in Ways You Hate

00:01:12.270 --> 00:01:14.070 align:middle line:90%
and What You Can Do About It."

00:01:14.070 --> 00:01:15.450 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:16.410 align:middle line:90%
Irwin.

00:01:16.410 --> 00:01:17.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Thanks for having me.

00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:21.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Wisdom television is very,
very pleased to welcome you

00:01:21.750 --> 00:01:24.720 align:middle line:84%
because there's not one
person I know out there who

00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:29.480 align:middle line:84%
doesn't behave in ways
they hate sometimes.

00:01:29.480 --> 00:01:34.690 align:middle line:84%
Is it true that you can change
when you get into so much pain

00:01:34.690 --> 00:01:38.350 align:middle line:90%
that you can't stand it anymore?

00:01:38.350 --> 00:01:40.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Most people can't.

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:44.130 align:middle line:10%
And they are doomed to repeating
unpleasant experiences.

00:01:44.130 --> 00:01:48.890 align:middle line:10%
As opposed to a child who
burns their hand on a hot stove

00:01:48.890 --> 00:01:51.470 align:middle line:10%
and learns not to do
it again, most of us

00:01:51.470 --> 00:01:55.110 align:middle line:10%
tend to repeat unpleasant
experiences over and over again

00:01:55.110 --> 00:01:58.670 align:middle line:10%
because we are motivated
by forces in our life

00:01:58.670 --> 00:02:00.840 align:middle line:10%
that we are not aware of.

00:02:00.840 --> 00:02:04.640 align:middle line:84%
And when we try to
change our behavior

00:02:04.640 --> 00:02:07.640 align:middle line:84%
and do well by
ourselves, ironically,

00:02:07.640 --> 00:02:09.919 align:middle line:90%
we end up feeling guilty.

00:02:09.919 --> 00:02:12.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Guilt is the basis of
everything that we're doing bad

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:13.280 align:middle line:90%
to ourselves.

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:14.080 align:middle line:90%
Do you think?

00:02:14.080 --> 00:02:15.230 align:middle line:90%
It has a lot to do with it.

00:02:15.230 --> 00:02:20.640 align:middle line:84%
Because when you are
a child growing up

00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:24.630 align:middle line:84%
in a family with flawed
parents, flawed siblings,

00:02:24.630 --> 00:02:28.050 align:middle line:84%
people who act badly on a
consistent, long-term basis

00:02:28.050 --> 00:02:31.820 align:middle line:84%
so that you can't
discount it, you

00:02:31.820 --> 00:02:34.460 align:middle line:84%
have a tendency, as a
child, to blame yourself

00:02:34.460 --> 00:02:35.420 align:middle line:90%
for what goes wrong.

00:02:35.420 --> 00:02:36.860 align:middle line:84%
Like the primitive
tribe in nature

00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:40.340 align:middle line:84%
when there are earthquakes and
floods and droughts and so on,

00:02:40.340 --> 00:02:41.400 align:middle line:90%
we've angered the gods.

00:02:41.400 --> 00:02:42.890 align:middle line:84%
It's our fault.
We have to atone.

00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:44.490 align:middle line:90%
>> We've angered our parents.

00:02:44.490 --> 00:02:45.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:49.760 align:middle line:84%
But parents behave in ways that
show that they are wounded.

00:02:49.760 --> 00:02:52.130 align:middle line:84%
They say things like,
you're ruining my life.

00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:54.020 align:middle line:84%
And you're driving
me to drink and--

00:02:54.020 --> 00:02:55.370 align:middle line:90%
>> How can you do this to me?

00:02:55.370 --> 00:02:59.403 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, how can you do this
to me, my thyroid, my head.

00:02:59.403 --> 00:03:00.320 align:middle line:90%
I hope your children--

00:03:00.320 --> 00:03:02.003 align:middle line:90%
>> You're giving me an ulcer.

00:03:02.003 --> 00:03:03.170 align:middle line:90%
>> You've given me an ulcer.

00:03:03.170 --> 00:03:05.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you've given me an ulcer.

00:03:05.280 --> 00:03:07.910 align:middle line:84%
And I hope your children do
to you what you've done to me.

00:03:07.910 --> 00:03:10.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Irwin, is there such a
thing as a functional family?

00:03:10.540 --> 00:03:11.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:16.030 align:middle line:84%
Because there's a large range
on the bell-shaped curve

00:03:16.030 --> 00:03:17.570 align:middle line:90%
of behaviors which are fine.

00:03:17.570 --> 00:03:20.270 align:middle line:84%
Children want to give
their parents good grades

00:03:20.270 --> 00:03:23.900 align:middle line:84%
and discount aberrations,
a bad day and so on.

00:03:23.900 --> 00:03:29.000 align:middle line:84%
But the problem is that we as
parents have our own childhood

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:32.870 align:middle line:84%
experiences which have created
flawed problems for us.

00:03:32.870 --> 00:03:34.790 align:middle line:84%
And we carry them over
with our children.

00:03:34.790 --> 00:03:35.990 align:middle line:90%
And we don't change.

00:03:35.990 --> 00:03:39.200 align:middle line:84%
You know that the adults
that you know who act badly

00:03:39.200 --> 00:03:42.110 align:middle line:84%
do it consistently for
years and years and years.

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:45.080 align:middle line:10%
So a child can't
discount something bad

00:03:45.080 --> 00:03:47.810 align:middle line:10%
happening as a bad day.

00:03:47.810 --> 00:03:48.920 align:middle line:90%
Parents act badly.

00:03:48.920 --> 00:03:50.690 align:middle line:90%
They pout and they get angry.

00:03:50.690 --> 00:03:52.640 align:middle line:84%
And they reject
their children and do

00:03:52.640 --> 00:03:55.010 align:middle line:84%
all kinds of things which
show that they are wounded.

00:03:55.010 --> 00:03:56.390 align:middle line:90%
And children feel guilty.

00:03:56.390 --> 00:03:58.730 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, they have
to inhibit something

00:03:58.730 --> 00:04:01.300 align:middle line:90%
which is good for them.

00:04:01.300 --> 00:04:03.880 align:middle line:84%
An overprotective parent
is a very simple example

00:04:03.880 --> 00:04:07.860 align:middle line:90%
for your audience to read.

00:04:07.860 --> 00:04:10.170 align:middle line:84%
You're out there playing and
having fun and spontaneous

00:04:10.170 --> 00:04:11.850 align:middle line:84%
and riding your bike
and doing sports.

00:04:11.850 --> 00:04:15.270 align:middle line:84%
And your mother or father,
whoever it is, is frantic.

00:04:15.270 --> 00:04:16.260 align:middle line:90%
Getting crazy.

00:04:16.260 --> 00:04:17.385 align:middle line:90%
You're going to get killed.

00:04:17.385 --> 00:04:18.279 align:middle line:90%
How can you do this?

00:04:18.279 --> 00:04:19.620 align:middle line:84%
>> There are bad
people out there.

00:04:19.620 --> 00:04:20.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:04:20.420 --> 00:04:21.665 align:middle line:90%
And they're getting agitated.

00:04:21.665 --> 00:04:23.790 align:middle line:84%
So you're having fun and
doing what's good for you.

00:04:23.790 --> 00:04:26.850 align:middle line:84%
And you see your parent losing
it, going off the deep end.

00:04:26.850 --> 00:04:28.530 align:middle line:90%
You are causing that.

00:04:28.530 --> 00:04:31.740 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, you
become cautious

00:04:31.740 --> 00:04:35.850 align:middle line:84%
and inhibited as a result of
feeling guilty about ruining

00:04:35.850 --> 00:04:38.190 align:middle line:90%
your parent for having fun.

00:04:38.190 --> 00:04:39.778 align:middle line:90%
You don't want to be cautious.

00:04:39.778 --> 00:04:41.070 align:middle line:90%
You don't want to be inhibited.

00:04:41.070 --> 00:04:42.778 align:middle line:84%
But you go through
life feeling that way.

00:04:42.778 --> 00:04:45.210 align:middle line:84%
And you can't understand
why you can't change.

00:04:45.210 --> 00:04:46.650 align:middle line:90%
You can't go on ski trips.

00:04:46.650 --> 00:04:49.710 align:middle line:84%
You can't allow yourself
to fly in a plane

00:04:49.710 --> 00:04:51.720 align:middle line:90%
or do sports and so on.

00:04:51.720 --> 00:04:53.400 align:middle line:84%
Because every time
you do, you start

00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:56.490 align:middle line:84%
to feel guilty which is
associated historically

00:04:56.490 --> 00:04:58.710 align:middle line:84%
with ruining someone
else, ruining a parent.

00:04:58.710 --> 00:05:01.772 align:middle line:84%
Now, you could
rebel against that.

00:05:01.772 --> 00:05:04.230 align:middle line:84%
You could say, oh, I'm not
going to limit myself and become

00:05:04.230 --> 00:05:04.860 align:middle line:90%
cautious.

00:05:04.860 --> 00:05:06.110 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm going to be a skydiver.

00:05:06.110 --> 00:05:08.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Skydiver, daredevil,
take chances, be wild,

00:05:08.790 --> 00:05:13.140 align:middle line:84%
ski off cliffs, and so on,
all of which are messages

00:05:13.140 --> 00:05:14.430 align:middle line:90%
to the parent.

00:05:14.430 --> 00:05:17.700 align:middle line:84%
I want you to recognize all
of your overprotectiveness

00:05:17.700 --> 00:05:19.480 align:middle line:90%
is ruining my life.

00:05:19.480 --> 00:05:21.095 align:middle line:84%
So these are like
neon signs which

00:05:21.095 --> 00:05:22.470 align:middle line:84%
get bigger and
bigger and bigger,

00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:23.610 align:middle line:90%
hoping the parent gets it.

00:05:23.610 --> 00:05:26.250 align:middle line:84%
But instead, the parent
gets more frantic.

00:05:26.250 --> 00:05:27.910 align:middle line:90%
You feel more guilty.

00:05:27.910 --> 00:05:31.020 align:middle line:84%
So the only alternative you have
is either to rebel against it

00:05:31.020 --> 00:05:32.820 align:middle line:84%
or to accommodate it
and become cautious.

00:05:32.820 --> 00:05:37.470 align:middle line:84%
>> So it's not-- when the child
starts to become very cautious

00:05:37.470 --> 00:05:41.240 align:middle line:84%
because the parent
is overprotective,

00:05:41.240 --> 00:05:44.120 align:middle line:84%
it's not necessarily
because the child is afraid.

00:05:44.120 --> 00:05:45.890 align:middle line:84%
But it's because
the child doesn't

00:05:45.890 --> 00:05:47.840 align:middle line:90%
want to displease the parents.

00:05:47.840 --> 00:05:48.890 align:middle line:90%
>> That's correct.

00:05:48.890 --> 00:05:50.330 align:middle line:84%
It's not that the
child is afraid.

00:05:50.330 --> 00:05:52.370 align:middle line:84%
It looks like the
child is afraid.

00:05:52.370 --> 00:05:55.820 align:middle line:84%
The actual fact is the child
is feeling guilty about hurting

00:05:55.820 --> 00:05:57.050 align:middle line:90%
someone else.

00:05:57.050 --> 00:05:58.793 align:middle line:84%
And when they grow
up, they vow they're

00:05:58.793 --> 00:06:00.710 align:middle line:84%
going to be different
with their own children.

00:06:00.710 --> 00:06:01.970 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
give them free rein

00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:03.262 align:middle line:90%
and encourage them to have fun.

00:06:03.262 --> 00:06:04.850 align:middle line:84%
And they act just
as overprotective

00:06:04.850 --> 00:06:08.180 align:middle line:84%
as their own parents
because they feel

00:06:08.180 --> 00:06:10.340 align:middle line:90%
they have hurt their parent.

00:06:10.340 --> 00:06:11.990 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, they
feel they deserve

00:06:11.990 --> 00:06:15.007 align:middle line:84%
to be hurt in return
by their own children.

00:06:15.007 --> 00:06:17.090 align:middle line:84%
The second reason, if you
do to your children what

00:06:17.090 --> 00:06:20.683 align:middle line:84%
was done to you, you don't have
to remember how unpleasant it

00:06:20.683 --> 00:06:22.850 align:middle line:84%
was for you when you were
a child because you're now

00:06:22.850 --> 00:06:24.830 align:middle line:84%
the doer instead
of the receiver.

00:06:24.830 --> 00:06:28.100 align:middle line:84%
So you can see with the example
of overprotection that happens.

00:06:28.100 --> 00:06:32.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, you can have it with a
child's school phobias-- kids

00:06:32.240 --> 00:06:35.180 align:middle line:84%
who are afraid to go to
school and leave home.

00:06:35.180 --> 00:06:37.070 align:middle line:90%
It looks like they're fearful.

00:06:37.070 --> 00:06:40.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, actually, they're guilty
about leaving a parent who

00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:42.170 align:middle line:84%
needs them, who's
possessive, who's

00:06:42.170 --> 00:06:45.510 align:middle line:84%
holding onto them, who needs
them to be close to the parent.

00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:48.170 align:middle line:84%
So they feel if they separate
and move away and have

00:06:48.170 --> 00:06:50.120 align:middle line:84%
other relationships
and enjoy school,

00:06:50.120 --> 00:06:52.250 align:middle line:84%
the parent will be
left out and hurt.

00:06:52.250 --> 00:06:54.830 align:middle line:84%
So they don't allow
themselves to move away.

00:06:54.830 --> 00:06:57.220 align:middle line:84%
That's the
overpossessive parent.

00:06:57.220 --> 00:07:00.920 align:middle line:84%
And in relation to a parent like
that, you grow up with values.

00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:03.950 align:middle line:84%
Loyalty is best,
loyalty at all costs.

00:07:03.950 --> 00:07:07.190 align:middle line:84%
>> And stick to your ethics,
even if it kills you.

00:07:07.190 --> 00:07:08.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Even if it kills you.

00:07:08.360 --> 00:07:10.130 align:middle line:84%
And with the
overprotective parent,

00:07:10.130 --> 00:07:13.630 align:middle line:84%
you grow up with a new
moral rule caution is best.

00:07:13.630 --> 00:07:15.650 align:middle line:84%
And with a parent who
is rejecting and doesn't

00:07:15.650 --> 00:07:19.190 align:middle line:84%
want you to be close, you
grow up with a new moral idea

00:07:19.190 --> 00:07:20.930 align:middle line:90%
independence is best.

00:07:20.930 --> 00:07:24.200 align:middle line:84%
And you can see from the charts
all of the new moral rules

00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:26.060 align:middle line:84%
that you create for
yourself and you live

00:07:26.060 --> 00:07:30.350 align:middle line:84%
your life by in a way
that's unfulfilled is

00:07:30.350 --> 00:07:35.150 align:middle line:84%
based on feeling guilty about
hurting a parent or a sibling.

00:07:35.150 --> 00:07:38.510 align:middle line:84%
And in order to protect
them, you restrict your life.

00:07:38.510 --> 00:07:42.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, do you think that
because of books like yours,

00:07:42.470 --> 00:07:45.110 align:middle line:84%
which is different than any
other self-help book I've seen,

00:07:45.110 --> 00:07:50.080 align:middle line:84%
by the way, in that you
go back and say, hey,

00:07:50.080 --> 00:07:53.400 align:middle line:84%
this is what happened, do you
think that we can get to be

00:07:53.400 --> 00:07:56.640 align:middle line:84%
better now than our
parents were for us?

00:07:56.640 --> 00:07:59.010 align:middle line:90%
Or does it always continue?

00:07:59.010 --> 00:08:02.070 align:middle line:84%
>> It continues until you
understand what the cause

00:08:02.070 --> 00:08:03.180 align:middle line:90%
of your problem is.

00:08:03.180 --> 00:08:06.810 align:middle line:84%
You need to recognize what
is operating in you to make

00:08:06.810 --> 00:08:08.400 align:middle line:90%
you behave in ways you hate.

00:08:08.400 --> 00:08:10.110 align:middle line:84%
And the only way
you can do that is

00:08:10.110 --> 00:08:12.390 align:middle line:84%
to see what happened
to you in relationship

00:08:12.390 --> 00:08:16.380 align:middle line:84%
to a dysfunctional parent
or sibling or family.

00:08:16.380 --> 00:08:18.090 align:middle line:90%
And that's what the charts do.

00:08:18.090 --> 00:08:20.700 align:middle line:84%
The charts help you recognize
exactly what happened

00:08:20.700 --> 00:08:25.600 align:middle line:84%
because you can see in one chart
all the flaws of your parents

00:08:25.600 --> 00:08:26.800 align:middle line:90%
and what happened to you.

00:08:26.800 --> 00:08:30.360 align:middle line:84%
Or in another chart, you
can see your worst problems

00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:32.669 align:middle line:84%
and look across and see
what happened to you.

00:08:32.669 --> 00:08:35.070 align:middle line:90%
Charts work like a mirror.

00:08:35.070 --> 00:08:36.960 align:middle line:84%
If you lived in an
era without mirrors--

00:08:36.960 --> 00:08:38.573 align:middle line:84%
and let's say you
thought, gee, I

00:08:38.573 --> 00:08:39.990 align:middle line:84%
don't think I'm
attractive enough.

00:08:39.990 --> 00:08:41.282 align:middle line:90%
I'd like to be more attractive.

00:08:41.282 --> 00:08:42.780 align:middle line:90%
There were no mirrors around.

00:08:42.780 --> 00:08:44.070 align:middle line:90%
Be very difficult to know.

00:08:44.070 --> 00:08:45.420 align:middle line:84%
>> You wouldn't know
whether you were attractive.

00:08:45.420 --> 00:08:46.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:08:46.220 --> 00:08:49.500 align:middle line:84%
You couldn't tell if was your
skin, your makeup, your eyes,

00:08:49.500 --> 00:08:52.410 align:middle line:84%
your hair that needed to be
adjusted or improved in order

00:08:52.410 --> 00:08:54.090 align:middle line:90%
to look more attractive.

00:08:54.090 --> 00:08:57.180 align:middle line:84%
It's exactly the same with
these charts in my book.

00:08:57.180 --> 00:09:00.480 align:middle line:84%
They help the reader to see
what it was that went wrong

00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:02.670 align:middle line:84%
and how they can
make it go right.

00:09:02.670 --> 00:09:05.250 align:middle line:84%
>> So in order to help, to
be a better parent then,

00:09:05.250 --> 00:09:07.950 align:middle line:84%
what you're saying is you've
got to cure yourself first

00:09:07.950 --> 00:09:10.530 align:middle line:84%
and understand
where you came from.

00:09:10.530 --> 00:09:13.350 align:middle line:90%
>> That's exactly correct.

00:09:13.350 --> 00:09:17.160 align:middle line:84%
And when I've spoken to
parent-teachers organizations,

00:09:17.160 --> 00:09:18.660 align:middle line:84%
I come in with a
different approach.

00:09:18.660 --> 00:09:20.910 align:middle line:84%
And they're always astounded
because I don't give them

00:09:20.910 --> 00:09:22.800 align:middle line:84%
advice on how to
raise their teenagers

00:09:22.800 --> 00:09:26.080 align:middle line:84%
and what they should do and what
they shouldn't do and so on.

00:09:26.080 --> 00:09:28.540 align:middle line:84%
Because we all know
the problem is we

00:09:28.540 --> 00:09:32.240 align:middle line:84%
don't know why we're not
doing the right thing.

00:09:32.240 --> 00:09:34.720 align:middle line:84%
And where you're
hung up is something

00:09:34.720 --> 00:09:37.150 align:middle line:84%
that can be overcome when you
have the correct knowledge.

